# =============================================================================
# Farm House — .gitignore
# Git ignores these paths so they are not committed. Lines starting with # are
# comments (Git supports comments in .gitignore).
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dependencies (npm)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Installed packages from npm. They can be huge and are reproducible from
# package.json + package-lock.json via `npm install`, so we never commit them.
node_modules/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project-specific (optional local files)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Practice / scratch script not part of the main app. Remove this line if you
# want basics.js tracked in git.
/basics.js

# Optional folder for local notes or exports (ignore if you use it for temp data).
txt/
/PROJECT_DESCRIPTION.md

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment and secrets
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If you later add API keys or ports in a .env file, keep it out of git.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logs and debug output
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
logs/
*.log

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Operating system junk
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / IDE (optional — some teams commit .vscode; here we ignore IDE noise)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment if you do not want to share editor settings:
# .vscode/
# *.swp
# *.swo
